  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse and an attempt to rectify the situation through partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence requested by the spectator is disproportionate and inconsistent with sentencing guidelines for this amount and defendant profile. Considering the mitigation of no prior record and partial repayment, a prison term of 6 months is deemed sufficient to address the criminality while acknowledging the defendant's potential for rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 6
}
